For wiki-rendered fields (_Description_, _Environment_, _Comments_, and _Free Text_ custom fields with wiki-rendering), using a \{noformat\} block is sometimes useful/necessary, particularly when text is imported from an external system.  However, \{noformat\} also strips out text wrapping, which can make text blocks very difficult to read.

In my opinion, "wrap" is not entirely a format, it's more of a display constraint. I believe the only time you want to avoid wrapping is when the content includes some space-formatted lines that need vertical alignment as well as horizontal (e.g. a space-formatted table).  In my experience, that's definitely not the majority use case.

Please implement text wrapping as the default behaviour for \{noformat\} blocks, and perhaps add *{{wrap=false}}* as a configurable option for those rare cases when wrapping is not desired.

